Millionaire adventurer Steve Fossett embarked on a solo, non-stop flight around the world in the Virgin Atlantic GlobalFlyer.
Facing challenges like GPS failures and turbulent jet streams, Fossett relies on the aircraft's aerodynamics and communication systems.
With support from Virgin Atlantic and Scaled Composites, Fossett aims to set a new record for endurance and piloting.
The journey not only tests his skills but also showcases advancements in aviation technology.
Fossett's determination and the innovative aircraft design by Burt Rutan mark a significant milestone in aviation history, pushing the boundaries of what is possible in flight.
